.TH "FORDPASS" "1" "May 31, 2026" "0.0.1" "pyfordpass"
.SH NAME
fordpass \- FordPass client and CLI
.sp
FordPass client and CLI. A third\-party reverse\-engineered client for the same private mobile\-app
endpoints the FordPass™ app uses, packaged as a Python library plus a \fBfordpass\fP command\-line
tool.
.SH DISCLAIMER
.sp
This project is \fBnot\fP an official Ford product. It is \fBnot\fP affiliated with, endorsed by,
sponsored by, or otherwise connected to Ford Motor Company or any of its subsidiaries. \(dqFordPass\(dq,
\(dqThe Lincoln Way\(dq, \(dqFord\(dq, and \(dqLincoln\(dq are trademarks of Ford Motor Company.
.sp
Because this client speaks to private endpoints rather than a documented public API, Ford may
change, throttle, or revoke access without notice \- and the maintainer cannot guarantee that any
particular feature will keep working.
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.IP "Warning"
.sp
\fBUse of this software may cause your FordPass™ / The Lincoln Way™ account to be (temporarily)
locked or suspended.\fP Traffic from any unofficial client can look anomalous to Ford\(aqs fraud
and abuse detection. \fBUse at your own risk.\fP
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
It is \fBstrongly recommended\fP to use a \fBseparate, secondary FordPass™ account\fP for this
software rather than your primary account:
.INDENT 0.0
.IP 1. 3
In the FordPass app on a phone (signed in as the primary owner), invite a secondary email
address as an additional driver for the vehicle. The invited address must be reachable from
that phone for verification.
.IP 2. 3
Sign up for a new FordPass account using that secondary email and accept the driver invitation.
.IP 3. 3
Configure \fBpyfordpass\fP (\fBfordpass auth login\fP) with the secondary account\(aqs credentials.
.UNINDENT
.sp
If the secondary account is later suspended, your primary account, warranty records, and
roadside\-assistance enrolment remain unaffected.
.sp
See the \X'tty: link https://github.com/marq24/ha-fordpass#general-disclaimer'\fI\%ha\-fordpass project\(aqs general disclaimer and account\-setup guidance\fP\X'tty: link' for the same procedure written up
from the Home Assistant integration\(aqs perspective \- the steps are identical regardless of which
third\-party client consumes the credentials.
.SH INSTALLATION
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
pip install pyfordpass
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Or with \fBuv\fP:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
uv tool install pyfordpass
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.SH QUICK START
.sp
The CLI is the primary surface. The library lives behind it for callers who want to integrate
against the same protocol the CLI uses. A typical first\-time flow:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
fordpass auth login       # Interactive sign\-in against the secondary account.
fordpass vehicle list     # See what\(aqs in the garage.
fordpass vehicle show VIN # Detailed view for one vehicle.
fordpass remote start VIN # Remote\-start command.
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Every subcommand supports \fB\-\-help\fP and most data\-returning subcommands support \fB\-\-json\fP for
machine\-readable output.
.sp
For programmatic use, see \fI\%fordpass.client.AsyncFordPassClient\fP (async HTTP client) and
\fI\%fordpass.sansio.FordPassClient\fP (sans\-I/O protocol core that builds
\fI\%fordpass.sansio.RequestDict\fP descriptors).
.SH CONFIGURATION
.sp
\fBpyfordpass\fP has two sets of optional settings, each managed with its own subcommand rather than
by editing files by hand. Both live under \fB~/.config/pyfordpass\fP on Linux (the platform\-specific
equivalent elsewhere).
.sp
\fBUser preferences\fP are managed with \fBfordpass config\fP\&. The most useful is a default VIN, so you
need not pass it to every command:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
# Set a default VIN, used whenever a command\(aqs VIN argument is omitted.
fordpass config set vehicle.default_vin VIN
# Distance (\(dqmi\(dq/\(dqkm\(dq) and temperature (\(dqF\(dq/\(dqC\(dq); both default from your locale.
fordpass config set units.distance mi
fordpass config set units.temperature C
# Default output format: \(dqpretty\(dq (Rich tables) or \(dqjson\(dq.
fordpass config set output.format json
# Show the effective configuration (defaults included), drop a key, or start over.
fordpass config dump
fordpass config delete units.distance
fordpass config reset
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fBAPI constants\fP are managed with \fBfordpass api\-config\fP\&. The built\-in defaults target Ford in
the USA, so most users never need to touch them. When Ford rotates a host or client ID you can
patch individual values without waiting for a new release; anything you set is merged over the
defaults, so only the changed keys are required:
.INDENT 0.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
.EX
# Override a single value; everything else falls back to the built\-in defaults.
fordpass api\-config set hosts.login https://login.ford.com
# Show the effective constants (defaults merged with overrides), or discard all overrides.
fordpass api\-config dump
fordpass api\-config reset
.EE
.UNINDENT
.UNINDENT
.sp
Values for other regions and for Lincoln can be copied from \X'tty: link https://github.com/marq24/ha-fordpass/blob/main/custom_components/fordpass/const.py'\fI\%ha\-fordpass const.py\fP\X'tty: link'\&.
